ry—including not only the Doctrine of Right, the Critiques, and the political essays but also Kant’s lectures and minor writings—the volume’s distinguished contributors demonstrate that Kant’s philosophy offers compelling positions that continue to inspire the best thinking on politics today.Aside from the editor, the contributors are Michaele Ferguson, Louis-Philippe Hodgson, Ian Hunter, John Christian Laursen, Mika LaVaque-Manty, Onora O’Neill, Thomas W. Pogge, Arthur Ripstein, and Robert S. Taylor.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  a.  a9780271052595.  aArthur Ripstein.  aCritique of Pure Reason.  aJohn Christian.  aKant political theory.  aKantian ethics.  aLaVaque-Manty.  aLaursen Mika.  aLouis-Philippe Hodgson Ian Hunter.  aMichaele Ferguson.  aOnora O’Neill.  aRobert S. Taylor.  aThomas W. Pogge.1 aEllis, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEllis, Elisabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFerguson, Michaele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHodgson, Louis-Philippe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunter, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaVaque-Manty, Mika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaursen, John Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Neill, Onora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPogge, Thomas W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRipstein, Arthur, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Robert S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.go